fields.description:
As an Org Admin it would be helpful to be warned that emails will be sent to users once the domain is claimed/verified. 

Adding to our documentation on Organization Administration: https://confluence.atlassian.com/cloud/organization-administration-938859734.html

Suggest adding a note that upon completing step 4, emails will be generated: 
{quote}
4. Verify your ownership of one or more domains to manage the Atlassian accounts that use email addresses with those domains.
{quote}

As well as our documentation on Domain Verification:
https://confluence.atlassian.com/cloud/domain-verification-873871234.html

Suggest adding a note around where it says: 
{quote}
All the Atlassian accounts with email addresses from those domains become managed by your organization. 
{quote}

Suggesting we promote the second to last bullet point to the top: 
{quote}
During the time it takes to configure SAML single sign-on, users won't be able to log in to your Atlassian Cloud applications. Consider scheduling a day and time for the changeover to SAML, and alerting your users in advance.
{quote}
Additionally, it would be great to add something along these lines as the _first_ or _second_ bullet point:
{quote}
Make sure you have at least one admin level account that isn't part of the domains you have verified. That way, you can still access your account if any SAML settings are incorrect.
{quote}
